ciMbb2TVrEl493Sy4ddFBmLcis-Ko0Ssy1pNvLr9HqsTJ8kZqbxvfbyxA4wcjBCcRszw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Explaining failure reasons**\\n\\nI need to provide a concise explanation of why it failed, including the fix and the commit hash. It's possible to mention the untracked metadata directory if it's relevant. I could also note that I removed an impossible test since Class.forName in the 2.2 branch throws a ClassNotFoundException instead of returning null, making the fallback line unreachable on the JVM. I might suggest rerunning it as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "That failure makes sense.\n\nCause:\n- In `commons-io:commons-io:2.2`, `ClassLoaderObjectInputStream.resolveClass(...)` does:\n  - `Class.forName(name, false, classLoader)`\n  - then only falls back if that call returns `null`\n- On the JVM, `Class.forName(...)` does not return `null` here; it throws `ClassNotFoundException`.\n- So the test I added was invalid for `2.2` and triggered exactly that exception.\n\nFix applied:\n- Removed the unsupported fallback test from:\n  - `tests/src/commons-io/commons-io/2.2/src/test/java/commons_io/commons_io/ClassLoaderObjectInputStreamTest.java`\n\nCommit:\n- `3a2223b72` — `Remove unsupported commons-io 2.2 fallback test`\n\nYou can rerun:\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=commons-io:commons-io:2.2`\n\nNote:\n- The uncovered `resolveClass` fallback in `2.2` appears effectively unreachable in normal JVM execution.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_090b8e9a0eecd2120169efef40eb58819f9be6c37525560998\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 231, "output": 301, "cacheRead": 27392, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27924, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777332029444, "responseId": "resp_090b8e9a0eecd2120169efef3e18f8819f88e9e285bbd79cf6"}}
